HEADWORD: Subaerial
<hw>Sub`a*e"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Beneath the sky;
in the open air; specifically <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, taking place on the
earth's surface, as opposed to <xex>subaqueous</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subagency</ent>⟦br⟧
